description:
Provide comprehensive customization options, agent management, settings UI, and help resources.

## Overview

EP7 is the polish phase that transforms the dashboard from a functional tool into a refined, customizable workspace. It covers user preferences, agent configuration, comprehensive settings, and integrated help resources.

## Core Features

### 1. Agent Management
- **Agent Registry**: List available Claude Code agents with descriptions
- **Custom Agents**: Create project-specific agents with custom system prompts
- **Agent Assignment**: Associate agents with specific beads or issue types
- **Agent History**: Track which agents worked on which issues

### 2. Settings UI
- **Appearance**: Theme (light/dark/auto), font size, density (compact/comfortable)
- **Behavior**: Auto-refresh interval, notification preferences, keyboard shortcuts
- **Integrations**: Claude API key status, CodeGraph connection, Beads CLI path
- **Data**: Export/import settings, clear cache, reset to defaults

### 3. Customization Options
- **Kanban Columns**: Show/hide columns, custom column ordering
- **Card Display**: Choose visible fields (priority, labels, assignee, due date)
- **Default Views**: Set preferred tab, filters, and sort order per project
- **Keyboard Shortcuts**: Customizable keybindings for common actions

### 4. FAQ & Help Resources
- **Integrated Help Panel**: Searchable FAQ within the dashboard
- **Contextual Tips**: Smart tooltips explaining features on hover
- **Onboarding Flow**: First-run walkthrough for new users
- **Documentation Links**: Quick access to Beads, Claude Code, and dashboard docs

## Acceptance Criteria

### Agent Management
- [ ] Agent list panel showing available agents with descriptions
- [ ] Create custom agent form with name, description, system prompt fields
- [ ] Agent selector when starting a chat session
- [ ] Agent activity visible in observability panel (connects to EP5)

### Settings
- [ ] Dedicated Settings page accessible from navigation
- [ ] All settings persist to localStorage
- [ ] Settings export as JSON, import validates schema
- [ ] Reset button with confirmation dialog

### Customization
- [ ] Drag-to-reorder Kanban columns
- [ ] Toggle card field visibility in settings
- [ ] Saved filter presets per project

### Help
- [ ] Help icon in header opens FAQ panel
- [ ] Cmd+? keyboard shortcut opens help
- [ ] Search within FAQ content
- [ ] "What's New" changelog accessible from help

## Implementation Notes

### Data Model
```typescript
interface DashboardSettings {
  appearance: {
    theme: 'light' | 'dark' | 'auto';
    fontSize: 'small' | 'medium' | 'large';
    density: 'compact' | 'comfortable';
  };
  behavior: {
    autoRefreshMs: number;
    notifications: boolean;
    soundEnabled: boolean;
  };
  kanban: {
    columnOrder: string[];
    hiddenColumns: string[];
    cardFields: string[];
  };
  shortcuts: Record<string, string>;
}

interface CustomAgent {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  systemPrompt: string;
  createdAt: string;
  projectId?: string;  // null = global
}
```

### UI Components to Create
- SettingsPage.svelte - full settings UI with tabs
- AgentManagerPanel.svelte - list/create/edit agents
- CustomAgentForm.svelte - agent creation form
- HelpPanel.svelte - FAQ and help content
- KeyboardShortcutsPanel.svelte - shortcut customization
- OnboardingModal.svelte - first-run experience

### Key Integration Points
- Settings stored in localStorage with version migration
- Agents stored in beads metadata or local JSON
- Help content can be markdown files loaded at runtime
- Theme CSS variables for appearance changes
